Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa president believes the fight against HIV/Aids should be a collaborative effort. PRETORIA - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has urged all South Africans to participate in the development of a new strategic plan to end HIV/Aids by 2030. Ramaphosa spoke at a meeting of the South African National Aids Council in Pretoria on Friday.The deputy president said the fight against HIV/Aids should be a collaborative effort. I urge all of us to take part in the development process. Let us ensure that the various constituencies that we represent also contribute their ideas. He added that government s goal was clear. It is in our hands. By working together we must end Aids by 2030. The theme for International Aids Day on 1 December is, It Is in Our Hands to End HIV and TB .(Edited by Shimoney Regter)